feat: user management + ticket reassignment + drop vendors

Aligns the build with PROBLEM_STATEMENT.pdf and fixes three bugs the user
reported:

  1) Network engineers could not assign tickets to field engineers.
     The backend only had PATCH /api/v1/tickets/{id} for status; there
     was no way to change assignedTo after creation. Added:
       PATCH /api/v1/tickets/{id}/assign?assignedToId=X
     plus a corresponding "Assign / Reassign" action in the row menu
     on Tickets page (visible to ADMIN, MANAGER, NETWORK_ENGINEER).
     Dialog lists only ACTIVE users with engineer roles.

  2) Admin could not delete a user. Added:
       DELETE /users/{userId}   (ADMIN-only, hard delete)
     with a confirmation dialog warning about FK references.

  3) Admin could change user to SUSPENDED but had no way to revert.
     Added:
       PUT /unblock-user?userId=X   (flips SUSPENDED -> ACTIVE)
     plus an "Approve account" action for INACTIVE users from the same
     menu. The Admin > Users page is now a fully managed table:
       - Change role  (modal with all 5 roles)
       - Block / unblock / approve  (status-aware action surfaces only the right one)
       - Delete       (confirm dialog)
     Self-edit is blocked: you can't touch your own row.

Other:
- Gateway predicates updated to include /users/** and /unblock-user.
- SpringSecurity matcher updated to gate the new endpoints with hasRole(ADMIN).
- Tasks-list "Assign user" dropdown was showing "- ROLE" because the
  template used u.username; backend DTO exposes name. Fixed.
- Dropped Vendors module entirely per request: removed feature folder,
  removed route, removed sidebar nav, removed dashboard tile, removed
  api.service method. Backend Vendor controller left in place (would
  require coordinated DB migration to fully drop).

Files changed:
- backend/user-service: UserController, UserService(Impl), SpringSecurity
- backend/incident-service: IncidentTicketController, IncidentTicketService(Impl)
- backend/api-gateway: application.properties
- frontend/core/services: api.service.ts, dashboard.service.ts
- frontend/features/admin: users-list.component.ts (full rewrite)
- frontend/features/tickets: tickets-list.component.ts (add Assign dialog)
- frontend/features/tasks: tasks-list.component.ts (u.username -> u.name)
- frontend/features/layout: layout.component.ts (drop Vendors title)
- frontend/app.routes.ts: drop /vendors route
- frontend/features/vendors: directory removed
